This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with person re-identification, which is a common problem in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel memory network to improve the performance of unsupervised cross-domain Re-ID, which involves learning from unlabelled data, making it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also uses memory modules to store representations of the target domain, which is a common technique in Memory Networks (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
